              protocols are often immature and lack adequate functional
              activity both at the single-cell and network levels unless the
              neurons are cultured for several months. Partially due to these
              limitations, the functional properties of hiPSC-derived neuronal
              networks are still not well characterized. Here, we adapt a
              recently published protocol that describes production of human
              neurons from hiPSCs by forced expression of the transcription
              factor neurogenin-212. This protocol is rapid (yielding mature
